  <title>
    
    
    <phrase>Show Rulers</phrase>
    
    
    
    
    
    
  </title>

  
  
  <indexterm significance="normal">
    <primary>Rulers</primary>
    <secondary>Show/Mask rulers</secondary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm significance="normal"><primary>Show Rulers</primary></indexterm>
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  
  


  

  
  

  <para>
    The <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Show Rulers</guimenuitem> command enables and disables
    displaying the rulers. It may be useful to disable them if you are
    working in <link linkend="gimp-view-fullscreen">full-screen mode</link>.
  </para>
  <para>  <!--Added 050611-->
    You can set the default for the rulers in the
    <link linkend="gimp-prefs-image-window">Image Window Appearance</link>
    dialog.
  </para>

  
  

  
  

  
  

  
  

  
  

  


  <sect3>
    <title>
      <phrase>Activating the Command</phrase>
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
      
    </title>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        
        
        <para>
          You can access this command from the image menubar through
          <menuchoice moreinfo="none">
            <guimenu moreinfo="none"><accel>V</accel>iew</guimenu>
            <guimenuitem moreinfo="none">Show R<accel>u</accel>lers</guimenuitem>
          </menuchoice>,
        </para>
        
        
        
        
        
        
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        

        <para>
          or by using the keyboard shortcut
          <keycombo moreinfo="none">
            <keycap moreinfo="none">Shift</keycap><keycap moreinfo="none">Ctrl</keycap><keycap moreinfo="none">R</keycap>
          </keycombo>.
        </para>

        

        

        

        

        

        

        
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </sect3>
</sect2>
